name: BIBO M2 E2 left E1 Ditto BLTouch

printer_notes.3.0.0: Do not remove the following keywords! These keywords are used in the "compatible printer" condition of the print and filament profiles to link the particular print and filament profiles to this printer profile.\nPRINTER_VENDOR_BIBO\nPRINTER_MODEL_BIBO2

before_layer_gcode.3.0.0:
;BEFORE_LAYER_CHANGE
;[layer_z]
M104 S{temperature[0]} T0 ; set 1st nozzle heater to print temperature
G92 E0

deretract_speed.3.0.0: 0 # By setting this value to 0 deretract used the retract_speed

printer_settings_id.3.0.0: BIBO M2 E2 left E1 Ditto BLTouch

end_gcode.3.0.0:
;BIBO End GCode
M107 ; turn fans off
G91 ; Relative positioning
G1 Z1 F100
M140 S0    ; Disable heated bed
M104 T0 S0 ; extruder T0 heater off
M104 T1 S0 ; extruder T1 heater off
G1 Z+0.5 X-20 Y-20 F300 ; move Z down then move print head a bit out of the way
G28 X0 Y0 ; move X/Y to min endstops, so the head is out of the way
G90    ; Absolute positioning
G92 E0.0 ; Reset extruder position
M84    ; Turn steppers off
M605 S2 E0 ; Turn off Ditto Printing function
M117 BIBO Print complete ; Put print complete message on screen

start_gcode.3.0.0:
;Start code PrusaSlicer BIBO 2 printers E2 left (i.e. T1) E1 Ditto With Marlin 2 and BLTouch
M605 S2 E1 ; Turn on Ditto Printing
G21  ; set units to metric
G90  ; absolute positioning
M107 ; start with the fan off
M140 S{first_layer_bed_temperature[0] - 5} ; set bed temp
M190 S{first_layer_bed_temperature[0]} ; wait for bed temp
M104 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} T0 ; set 1st nozzle heater to ditto print temperature
M104 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} T1 ; set 2nd nozzle heater to first layer temperature
M109 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} T0 ; set 1st nozzle heater to ditto printing temperature
M109 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} T1 ; Wait for 2nd nozzle heater to first layer temperature
T0   ; Start at T0 to avoid extruder nozzle offset issues
G28 X0 Y0  ; move X/Y to min endstops
G28 Z0     ; move Z to min endstops
G29              ; Auto bed-level (BL-Touch) with just the bed heated
G1 Z2 F400 ; move the print bed down 2mm
G92 E0.0 ; zero the current extruder coordinate
G1 Y0 F1200 E0 ; move Y to min endstop and reset extruder
G92 E0.0 ; zero the current extruder coordinate
T1 ; switch to tool position T1
G92 E0.0 ; zero the current extruder coordinate
M117 E2 nozzle wipe... ; Put Nozzle wipe message on screen, Attempt Nozzle Wipe (for ooze free startup)
G1 X-15.0 Y-92.9 Z0.3 F2400.0       ; move to start-line position
G1 X15.0 Y-92.9 Z0.3 F1000.0 E2     ; draw 1st line
G1 X15.0 Y-92.6 Z0.3 F3000.0        ; move to side a little
G1 X-15.0 Y-92.6 Z0.3 F1000.0 E4    ; draw 2nd line
G1 X-15.0 Y-92.3 Z0.3 F3000.0       ; move to side a little
G1 X15.0 Y-92.3 Z0.3 F1000.0 E6     ; draw 3rd line
G1 X15.0 Y-92 Z0.3 F3000.0          ; move to side a little
G1 X-15.0 Y-92 Z0.3 F1000.0 E8      ; draw 4th line
G92 E0.0 ; reset extruder coordinate to zero before printing
M117 BIBO Now Printing from E2... ; Put now printing message on screen
